  <p>During December, amendments to the Infonavit and Fovissste legislation were approved, which are intended to allow, among other things, unemployed
    members of the Infonavit to obtain mortgage loans; in addition, workers will have the opportunity to be granted additional loans, as soon as they settle
    the current one, without co-participation of the commercial banks.</p>

  <p>According to Carlos Martínez, Head of Infonavit, these amendments will drive origination of financing options properly suited to the needs of workers
    during 2021. It is worth noting that in December, Infonavit achieved its highest amount of granted mortgage loans in the last five years, of which over
    70% were for the acquisition of new or existing housing.</p>

